08/10/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- World Bank Vice President Shigeo Katsu praised Albania's progress in implementing projects aimed at promoting social and economic development, local dailies reported Thursday (7 October). 
Katsu met with Albanian Finance Minister Arben Malaj on the sidelines of the Bank's annual meeting in Washington.
In other news Thursday, Tirana's Court of Appeals upheld a lower court ruling that acquitted the ex-director of the country's intelligence service, Fatos Klosi, of abuse of power. 
Prosecutors had argued he used his authority to influence 15 public procurement tenders. 
(Albanian Daily News - 08/10/04; Albanian Daily News - 07/10/04)
